Constructor Detail

DateField

public DateField()
Initializes this field. Note, that dates will be stored as strings into the database. Therefore the database type of this field is varchar and it's length is set to 19 characters, as this is the exact length of the date string.

Method Detail

getDateString

public String getDateString()
Creates the string representation of the date DataField.mValue is currently set to.

Format of that string is:
YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS

Returns:
String representation of DataField.mValue.

fromString

public void fromString(String date)
Constructs a Date object from the given string.
The String must be in the format: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.

date - String representing the date.

putData

public void putData(String key,
                    ContentValues values)
Description copied from interface: DatabaseField
When this field is serialized into the database this method is called. The field can then put it's data into the ContentValues variable under the given fieldName.

Parameters:
key - Key for the ContentValues variable and also name of this field in the object, that is being serialized.
values - ContentValues object holding all data, that will be written to the database.
